132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 885
H.P. 571 House of Representatives, March 4, 2025
An Act to Allow Certain Persons with a Permit to Carry Concealed
Handguns to Possess or Discharge a Firearm on School Property
Reference to the Committee on Judiciary suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative WHITE of Guilford.
Cosponsored by Senator HARRINGTON of York and
Representatives: BISHOP of Bucksport, EDER of Waterboro, FLYNN of Albion, LANCE of
Paris, LIBBY of Auburn, PAUL of Winterport, WHITE of Ellsworth, Senator: HAGGAN of
Penobscot.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 20-A MRSA §6552, sub-§2, ¶D is enacted to read:
3 D. The prohibition on the possession and discharge of a firearm does not apply to a
4 person 21 years of age or older who is not a student at that school and who possesses a
5 permit to carry a concealed handgun under Title 25, chapter 252.
6 SUMMARY
77 This bill allows a person to possess and discharge a firearm on school property if that
88 person is not a student at that school, is 21 years of age or older and possesses a permit to
99 carry a concealed handgun.
